About `document`
  `document` is a global variable that gives you access to the DOM

  `document.documentElement` returns the root, usually <html> element

  `document.body` returns <body>

  each DOM node has a nodeType property
    numeric code that identifies the type of node
    regular elements: 1
    text nodes: 3
    comments: 8

DOM Node Relationships
  all element nodes have a `childNodes` property that holds a NodeList array-like object

  firstChild
  parentNode
  previousSibling
  nextSibling
  lastChild

Find Elements
  document.getElementsByTagName("a")[1];

  getElementById
  getElementByClassName

Changing the Document
  removeChild
  appendChild
  insertBefore
  replaceChild
